				<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/90cbbb7b0d887ac6aaa2e68c38211d62?s=44&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D44&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /><cite><b class="fn">Tj</b> </cite><a href="http://shootingthebull.net/blog/best-weapon-for-home-defense/#comment-453"><time datetime="2014-01-25T22:15:28+00:00">January 25, 2014 at 10:15 pm</time></a>			</header><!-- .comment-meta -->

			
			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>I absolutely agree and personally I have never thought home carry was being &#8220;paranoid&#8221;. I&#8217;ve got anti-kick plates ( <a href="http://doordevil.com" rel="nofollow">http://doordevil.com</a> ) on all my exterior doors too, only about 80 bucks a piece, so not a lot of money for the extra peace of mind IMO.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply">
				<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/blog/best-weapon-for-home-defense/?replytocom=453#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-453", "453", "respond", "159")'>Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span>			</div><!-- .reply -->
